I wasn't paying attention to every game listed in this video, so not sure which ones you might be looking at, but are you taking into account the big difference in performance between the lower resolution comparisons and 4k comparisons?

It looked like in the lower res comparisons it was as you mention here, but in the 4k comparisons the 9070 XT often closed the gap or even out-performed the 7900 XTX. Though this was highly dependent on the game tested, so maybe some others are testing different games?

@hardwareunboxed can you guy say something abut driver stability? I experienced some issues Wirth 25.3.1 and my Red Devil 9070Xt. Hogwards Legacy causes driver time outs while Ray Tracing and FSR 3 is active - runs perfectly without RT. Diablo 4 causes driver time outs after 2-3 hours of play, making all screens go black for a minute, game crashes, driver restarts with the message that the driver was restarted due to a time out.

Did you experience issues with the drivers during your test runs? Can you tell us something about driver stability and quality of 25.3.1? This was missing in the review a bit knowing what AMD hat driver issues during the last couple of releases.

I know that I am an early adopter of those 9070XT cards and only in those two scenarios were incidents with the drivers. But more info from you guys would be much appreciated. Maybe a video regarding AMD driver status/Stability with the new cards including your experiences during testing would be a great idea.

