@denxos I mean, its 50/50. Yes, its alot of clutter, but its helpful.
We've established that alot of people are still hanging onto older cards from the 20 or even 10 series. GN does a good job in allowing people with those older cards to measure their uplift, without having to go to 3 separate videos. Especially important if you consider that basically no one else does this. HUB, LTT, J2C and many more only focus on the more recent stuff. The lowest i see in any of their videos is the 30 series from Nvidia or 6000 series from AMD so its hard if you have a 1070 and want to see if its worth it or not.
No doubt its alot of clutter, but GN is more so of the nerd channel than HUB or LTT. We like graphs, and alot of it. Its catering to the audience if you ask me.

@phantommodding1025 You seem to have misunderstood something. What part of "[Nvidia] has destroyed all semblance of value" did you interpret as me glazing them?

As for AMD, 550-450 would have been enough to make up for the lack of performance compared to their marketing (again), as well as make an actual gap between their two products so they don't have to drop prices for the lower specced one (again). Like I said, the current 600-550 pricing will let AMD keep their foot in the door, but not much more than that. This was their greatest chance to truly go on the offensive and regain tons of market share, yet they held back. Defending that helps no one.

You're right about AIBs though, some of them are really out of control these days. But they're not the only problem.

